body:
I can see the following problem implementing this feature:

Usually defaultRoles are implicitly given to the all users but, in fact common practice is that such a roles are used with some rules and that rules may require some context params that are passed as 3rd param `Rule::execute()`. So simple doing something like in:

`PhpManager::getRolesByUser($userId)`

``` php
$deafultRoles = array_filter($this->defaultRoles, function($role) {
  return $this->checkAccess($userId, $role);
})
```

will make no sense due to lack of `$params` that should be passed to `checkAccess`.
any ideas @samdark ?
